”’Ů@875667853bf87298734c634b9b4ce6a7977580d31120bab1dfe2dd2ea930fb15ÚlTitle: This week in Nushell #212
Path: Nushell
Content:
amtoine 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/10373] fixed the pretty printing of failing tests in std
, and 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/10339] added a 
``std repeat``
 command to replace 
``"foo" * 3``
, and 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/10299] added a case-insensitive example to 
``where``
, and 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/10286] allowed 
``into duration``
 to take an integer amount of ns
zhiburt made several fixes to table rendering: 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/10367] 1
, 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/10357] 2
, 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/10351] 3
jntrnr 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/10360] fixed 'let' to properly redirect
, and 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/10338] changed 
``echo``
 to print when not redirected
, and 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/10325] removed profiling from nushell's hot loop
GomesGoncalo 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/10356] made a fix to allow json requests of value type list
fdncred 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/10354] added a helper switch to move cursor to end of buffer
, and 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/10344] added a few more columns to linux 
``ps -l``
 output
, and 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/10294] silenced some ucp warnings
, and 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/10264] allowed update to use metadata
sholderbach 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/10353] optimized the use of range in 
``std repeat``
, and 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/10333] updated internal use of 
``decimal``
 to 
``float``
, and 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/10328] made a change to use slices directly instead of 
``&Vec``
, and 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/10321] deref 
``&String``
 arguments to 
``&str``
 where appropriate
, and 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/10320] renamed 
``random decimal``
 to 
``random float``
, and 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/10315] inverted 
``&Option``
s to 
``Option<&T>``
, and 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/10314] bumped 
``calamine``
, and 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/10313] updated 
``crates-ci/typos``
 and fixed new typos
, and 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/10293] removed python-like string multiplication
, and 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/10292] removed pythonic 
``int * list``
 behavior
, and 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/9979] renamed 
``into decimal``
 to 
``into float``
Tiggax 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/10350] removed 
``select``
 error if same row/column is provided
, and 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/10216] updated 
``reject``
 to be able to recive arg list
, and 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/10163] updated 
``reject``
 to support multiple row args
WindSoilder 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/10347] updated 
``ps``
 to add 
``cwd``
 column on linux and macos
hustcer 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/10334] updated Nu to v0.84 for release and nightly-build
, and 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/10331] upgraded softprops/action-gh-release to v0.1.15 for release and nightly build workflow
kubouch 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/10326] allowed parse-time evaluation of 
``if``
, and 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/10324] removed leftover const eval file
dmatos2012 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/10304] fixed variables not allowed in ucp
geniusisme 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/10302] made a change to provide env to commands and try to start provided path
dzorya 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/10291] added a comment that perl is required for feature static-link-opensslâ€¦
nibon7 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/10289] made cursor_shape optional
alsuren 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/10287] signposted 'input list --types 
[
key
]
' from 'keybindings list'
utouto97 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/10283] added 'from ndjson' into standard library
IanManske 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/10282] fixed 
``rm``
 on macOS
nanoqsh 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/10249] made a change to keep order for 
``par-each``
J-Kappes 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/10235] fixed input --until-bytes: now stops at any of given bytes
